First things first, new video is back up on the channel so go have a look (link in bio)... Secondly.... apparently all I eat is ice-cream and cereal 🤔 Real talk part 2👉🏼 Following on from yesterday’s great response on some social media real talk “body edition”, I thought I’d follow up with a “food edition” as, based on yesterday’s poll on my story, you want me to start posting some more food pics BUT 👇🏼
➖
Again, whether it’s me or anyone else you follow on IG who’s part of this “fitfam”, take SOME of the food pics we post with a pinch of salt. I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again. Though “fitfammers” post A LOT of foodporn that may not be considered quote on quote “healthy”, they are NOT what our diets mostly comprise of. People don’t like pics of chicken and broccoli. They like pics of chocolate bars shoved into Ben and Jerry’s with whipped cream on top. So, you know what fitfammers do? Every NOW AND THEN... when they have a less “clean” meal, they take advantage by taking a picture (sometimes a LOT of pictures so that they have more to post later) of it and eventually clock up a “storage” of foodporn pics to post. The result?👇🏼
➖
From the outside (as a viewer) it may look as though person X eat like shit EVERY day when in reality its FAR from that and usually either 1-2x per week or just 1 meal here and there at the MOST with the REST (80%+ or 90% in my case) of their diet comprised completely of “bro food”. The pic you see here is an example of a normal “healthy meal” for me which I’d eat A LOT... I may have 2 of these per day, potentially with an extra “healthy” snack, hit a shit load of fibre, fruits and veggies and leave 10% of calories for the junk you may see but it’s NOT, and never will/should be the other way around.
➖
You want transparency so I’m giving it to you. Expect foodporn pics to come for sure. After all, with my amount of calories I can “afford” to have super foodporn but remember that the pics you may see are from that ODD (key word being odd) time I decide to substitute the above clean meal for a more “foodporn worthy” one and that they’re not a true representation of what I actually eat 90% of the time. Just sayin 🤓

Babpüré paprikás-dinsztelt hagymával 
Ha a mai ebédemet egyszóval kellene jellemezni akkor leginkább az egyszerűség jutna eszembe. 
Ahol éltem gyerekekként akkoriban gyakran került az asztalra. Azon a vidéken "tört paszulynak " hívták, hívják a mai napig. 
Zsenges babot feltettem annyi vízben főzni, hogy ellepje. Tettem bele 1 kis fej hagymát, 2 cikk fokhagymát, Himalája sót, kurkumat, fehérborsot, tarkonyt, majoránnat. Amikor megpuhult leontottem róla a vizet, adtam hozza zabkrémet, majd botmixerrel simara kevertem. 
Amíg a bab főtt elkészítettem a hagymát. 1 ek.Kókuszolajon/ kacsazsiron 3 fej felvágott vöröshagymat megdinszteltem. Fűszereztem Himalája sóval, pirospaprikaval. A kész ételt ezzel talaltam.

Blueberry Spinach Smoothie 🔋190 Calories
🔋19 g Carbs
🔋16 g Protein
🔋7 g Fat
⏰4 min.
🍹2 servings
☝️Another creative way to get spinach into your day is to add it to your smoothie. With the combination of your favorite protein powder and fresh fruit, you'll hardly notice the spinach—except for the lovely green color it imparts. This smoothie provides a great mix of proteins, carbohydrates, and dietary fats, and makes an excellent, well-balanced addition to your daily diet plan.
ℹ️Ingredients
* 	1 scoop vanilla protein powder
* 	1 cup frozen blueberries
* 	½ cup frozen peaches
* 	1 cup unsweetened almond milk
* 	1 cup baby spinach
* 	1 tbsp natural almond butter
* 	3 cubes ice
ℹ️Directions
Prep: 1 min.
Cook: 3 min.
Total: 4 min.
1. Place all ingredients in a blender and pulse blend until desired consistency is reached.

Fervi 2 litros de 🥛 (usei 1 de semi desnatado e outra de desnatado) com 3 🥄 de 🥛 em pó desnatado.
Quando levantou fervura desliguei o fogão. Depois de um tempo com o leite morno (quando da para aguentar colocar dedo por 3 segundos) adicionei 2 potes de iogurte integral a temperatura ambiente.
Tampei a panela e deixei no forno encubando das 20:30hs às 6:00hs da manhã do dia seguinte

INGREDIENTES⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
½ xícara (chá) de leite morno
1 colher (chá) de fermento biológico seco
1 colher (sopa) de açúcar cristal
⅓ de xícara (chá) de óleo
1 colher (chá) de sal
½ xícara (chá) de água
1 ovo
1 e ½ xícaras (chá) de farinha de trigo integral
1 e ¼ de xícaras (chá) de farinha de trigo
50g de sementes de abóbora torradas
1 gema para pincelar ⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀
MODO DE PREPARO⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀
Numa vasilha grande misture o leite morno com fermento e açúcar.
Em seguida, vá acrescentando na vasilha o óleo, o sal, a água e o ovo e continue misturando.
Por ultimo despeje a farinha de trigo integral misturada com a farinha de trigo.
Coloque as sementes de abóbora e misture.
Amasse bem a mistura até se obter uma massa lisa.
Deixe a massa descansar, coberta com um pano, até dobrar de volume.
Coloque em uma forma de bolo inglês untada com óleo.
Deixe dobrar de volume novamente.
Pincele com gema.
Leve ao forno a 200º por 25 ou 30min.

Vamos para a #receita de Molho de Tomate Caseiro 🍅 Anotem AÍ! 📃 VOCÊ VAI PRECISAR DE:
- Tomate: 2 quilos bem maduros, se possível, orgânicos
- Cebola: Duas grandes descascadas e cortadas em quatro
- Alho: Quatro dentes grandes descascados
- Cenoura: uma grande ou duas pequenas, se possível orgânicas
- Salsão: uma xícara picado (o talo e não as folhas)
- Alho porró: 1/2 xícara dele picado (a parte branca e não a verde)
🍲 MODO DE PREPARO:
- Lave todos os ingredientes.
- Corte os tomates, tire as sementes e junte-os às cebolas, alho, cenoura, salsão e alho porró também cortados. Coloque tudo na panela de pressão. Em 15 minutos (depois que iniciar a pressão) está pronto. Acredite, não precisa colocar água porque o tomate e a cebola soltam MUITA água.
- Desligue o fogo e deixe sair a pressão para abrir a panela.
- Aos poucos, coloque o conteúdo da panela no liquidificador e bata até virar uma espécie de suco grosso, consistente. Muito cuidado, pois o líquido está muito quente. Faça essa etapa em duas ou três vezes.
- Peneire o molho sobre a mesma panela que você usou para cozinhar os tomates.

caption:
Day 1 in Salzburg. What a picturesque city! Every angle was deep blue sky's and those greens that make you think some jacked the saturation on a photo. It is unreal. -- ALSO!! 1000 year old castle!!!! What!?!?? Incredible to walk up through the gate and imagine what it would have looked like  as it gradually stood the test of time. Inside was a really awesome timeline detailing various world events against it. -- Finally, dinner at Laschenskyhof ended with my favorite dessert ... hand made apple strudel...this is truly where my Grandmother's recipe is from. Down to the crust, it was perfect.

Por tanto @en.cubiertos decidió probar dicho plato que contiene medallones de lomo, caracterizados por su excelente textura, ternura y jugosidad, bordeados de tocineta y salsa de champiñones; como acompañante puedes escoger: papas a la francesa o puré de papa y ensalada. 
3 medallones muy bien preparados, compenetrados con la tocineta y la salsa. Lo pedimos bien asado y sin duda excelente corte! 🍴
El puré de muy buena textura, la ensalada le faltaba un poco más de vinagreta para que la lechuga se sintiera más fresca! 🥗

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Пян-се бывает с разными начинками, но я взяла у @pyansemoscow с сёмгой и грибами, и не прогадала. Теперь это мое любимое сочетание.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Я сначала не поверила, что им можно наесться часа на три. Но пян-се очень сытный. Перекусила и побежала изучать путеводители по Германии. Соединила Lonely planet, «Афишу», «Оранжевый гид» и рекомендации немецких блогеров. Так что посты о моей ноябрьской поездке должны быть максимально информативными. А пока остаётся гулять  по Кузнецкому мосту.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Rezept:
Pastinaken und Butternut-Kürbis mit dem Sparschäler die Schale entfernen. Das Fruchtfleisch ebenfalls mit dem Sparschäler in lange Streifen "schneiden". Beides Gemüse kurz in der Pfanne andünsten. Some people tell me I have amazing dedication, or iron willpower. Some people think i'm boring or missing out. None of these are true. What I am, is happy.

Don't you miss chocolate and cake? How do you live without wine at the weekends? Common questions. Firstly, I still eat chocolate, cake, and drink wine. Not in the quantities I used to, but I used to be unhappy. To me I can choose unhealthy and unhappy or I can choose healthiness and happiness. No decision required really.

It took me a year to lose the weight I needed to get to target. It took me another year to realise emotionally and psychologically that I was at target. Because often the emotional side of being overweight is much harder to lose than the weight itself and it took a long time for me to realise the fat girl was gone, and, not coming back! 
I can now fit in size 8 jeans, I can run about with the dogs and not get out of breath, I can get ready to go out without feeling desperately upset. And thanks to @slimmingworld and the support of my amazing group, I have energy, confidence, and a love for life I never had before.

I'm a target member and i'm happy!

The secret? Day after day. Week after week. Month after month relentless consistency📝

_

We live in a shortcut-hungry society and people want to get results without the hard work. That doesn’t fly. One thing I’ve always loved about training is that ‘the iron can’t lie’. Ruthless adherence and dedication applied to a base of knowledge and hunger to improve daily leads to results.

_

Helping others is something I love to be able to do. Not only because of the rewarding feeling when they see results, improve their training/mindset/life or something clicks with them but because many have taken the time to help me and teach me. I have been lucky enough to have some great mind and great physiques to learn from and if I can be that person to someone else then I’m doing something right😅

_

Trying to condense the last 6 months, no, the last 6/7 Years into a quick answer to ‘how do you get X’ isn’t easy but ANYONE can get the results they want if place importance upon the goals and prioritise training / nutrition / sleep! 
_

Es que cuando llevas un Estilo de Vida Saludable comes deliciosoooooo!!! Alguien recientemente me criticó por usar siempre el término "dietas locas". Me decía que había dedicación  detrás de crear esas dietas y que no debían ser criticadas. Luego de nuestra conversación entendió que carecen de fundamento o base científica, que llevan a daño metabólico, que no son sostenibles con el tiempo por lo restrictivas y desbalanceadas que son y que jamás podrán trabajar en mejorarte desde adentro hacia afuera y comprendió con ejemplos simples la diferencia entre un Estilo de Vida Saludable y una dieta loca. 
_________________________________________

Este pan de banana y pecanas es un #IrresistiblementeSaludable y les va a encantar!! Basado en un #EstiloDeVidaSaludable #healthylifestyle

RECETA... Ingredientes:
✔3/4tz de avena en hojuelas instantáneas ✔1/2tz de harina de almendras
✔1/4tz de linaza en polvo
✔1cdita de canela en polvo
✔3/4tz de pecanas
✔1/2tz de xylitol (Es un edulcorante. Pueden usar unos 5 a 7  sobrecitos de Stevia o el equivalente a 1/2cdita si no tienen Xylitol, dependiendo que tan dulce les guste)
✔1/2cdita de polvo de hornear
✔1/4cdita de bicarbonato
✔2 huevos enteros
✔2oz de queso crema tipo griego (1/2tz aproximadamente) [recomiendo usar yogur griego natural como alternativa]
✔2cdas de aceite de coco extra virgen ✔1cdita de extracto de vainilla ✔1banana grande bien madura
✔2cdas de miel de abejas

Preparación:
Precalienta el horno a 350°F. Prepara tu molde para pan con un poquitico de aceite en spray. 
Super simple ahora...Mezcla todos los secos por un lado y todos los húmedos por otro lado. 
Vierte los secos en los húmedos y mezcla hasta incorporar todo, pero sin sobre mezclar. 
Coloca en tu molde para pan y reserva.

caption:
12 октября по всей стране в честь открытия Христофором Колумбом Америки отмечается День Испании (Dia de la Hispanidad). Это праздник начала общения двух миров, символ мира и благополучия страны.
⠀⠀
🥘А в Торревьехе в эти дни в портовой части города с 11 по 15 октября проходит Севильская ярмарка (La Feria de Sevillanas). Ярмарка передаёт традиционное андалузское настроение, которое всегда стоит того, чтобы посетить и получить удовольствие.
⠀⠀
💃🏼В программе много интересных шоу, в том числе парад лошадей и шоу танцев фламенко. Также есть возможность попробовать традиционные блюда андалузской кухни из "casetas" (специальные возведенные шатры), основные мероприятия проходят в вечернее время.
⠀⠀ 🎶 Мы были там недолго сегодня днём, но на вечернее мероприятие не остались, слишком шумно, т.к. лучший шатёр будет награждён, из-за этого в каждом шатре звучит музыка или выступают исполнители.
🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸
Hispanic Day is celebrated throughout the country in honor of the discovery of America by Christopher Columbus. This is a celebration of the beginning of communication between two worlds, a symbol of peace and prosperity of the country.
⠀⠀
🥘The Seville Fair (La Feria de Sevillanas) is taking place in the port city from 11 to 15 October in Torrevieja. The fair conveys a traditional Andalusian mood, which is always worth visiting and enjoying it. 💃🏼The program is packed with many interesting shows, including a parade of horses and a flamenco dance show. There is also an opportunity to taste traditional Andalusian dishes from "casetas" (special built marquees), the main events take place in the evening.
⠀⠀ 🎶 We had a quick look this afternoon but didn't stay for the evening show as it was too noisy, as the best "caseta" will be awarded, because of this music played or singers/dancers performed in every marquee.

caption:
!! I'm always amazed to be asked to do an interview because I still feel like everything is new and everything new is a challenge 😳 but that means it was *such* an honor to do this interview with fellow NYC planner girl @bettes.pages for @project_kintsugi. We chatted about the importance of food in our lives and in Chinese culture, about the innovation and modernization happening in local Chinatown businesses spearheaded by the sons and daughters and even great great great granddaughters of the immigrant business owners, about dimsum and our many fond memories of it. As Bette wrote, I hope that @wontoninamillion not only makes you smile and reminds you of warm, delicious memories with your family, but that it also encourages you to eat more dimsum as a way of supporting Chinatown and immigrant-owned businesses everywhere. One of my favorite quotes: "An immigrant is an extreme person. No matter how bad circumstances are in your native country, regardless of the death threat, complacency and entropy means most people will stay put amid famine and genocide. Anyone who crosses deserts and mountains and oceans and borders because life means more to him than stillness is brave. Never disrespect an immigrant." (From Elizabeth Wurtzel's "Creatocracy") <3 Without further ado, check out the link in my profile for the full article. Thank you so much to @bettes.pages and @project_kintsugi for the opportunity!! Also, throwback photo! Wearing the original "I'm All A'BAO That Bass" tank 😆 (I miss my long hair 😢)

Lượng độ cực ít nhưng cực chất. Làm no nhanh nhưng ko ì ạch. Trang trí bắt mắt. Phục vụ đúng chuẩn 5*. Vào đây hầu như là dành cho khách thíck yên tĩnh. Ko náo động. Và mỗi bàn riêng biệt nói chuyện tâm sự to nhỏ. Yên ắng dễ chịu đến mức 1 tiếng dao vô tình cứa phải vào đĩa cũng trở nên khó nghe...

"sernikowy" omlet z masłem orzechowym 💛

Potrzebujemy:
• 2 białka jaj
• 1 żółtko
• 20g odżywki białkowej
• 17g budyniu waniliowego
• 60g twarogu
• łyżka proszku do pieczenia
• masło orzechowe

Białka jaj ubijamy na sztywną pianę, dodajemy żółtko i resztę składników (oprócz masła orzechowego) i mieszamy. Wylewamy do formy i pieczemy przez 20 minut w 180°. Gdy nasz omlet będzie już gotowy, smarujemy go masłem orzechowym.

T A R T A  de  E S P I N A C A !
Ahora si🙌 Receta 100% casera porque cuando empezas no hay vuelta atras y siempre queres TU masa. Pueden cambiar las harinas, las semillas, los condimentos y hacer la que para ustedes sea LO MAS MAS.
• Masa
> 1 taza harina avena
> 1/4 taza harina de lupino (o cualquier otra)
> 2 cdas semillas chia
> 2 cdas semillas lino
> 1 huevo
> 1 chorrito aceite de oliva
> 1 cdta polvo de hornear
> c/n agua (vayan agregando a pedido de la masa)
> 1 cdta curcuma
> sal y pimienta
🔛 Mezcla todo y anda agregando agua hasta formar una masa. Forra una tartera de silicona o apenas aceitada.
• Relleno
> 1 bolsa (500 grs) espinaca congelado de @magliavegetales (o 3 tazas cocidas y escurridas)
> 1 cebolla
> 1 huevo + 3 claras
> 2 rodajas queso port salut
> 2 cdas ricota
> 1 cda queso crema
> 1 cdta ajo en polvo
> sal y pimienta
🔛 Corta la cebolla y salteala en una sarten con un toque de oliva y agua. Integra todos los ingredientes y procesa solo una parte(cita) asi se siente el relleno y no es todo una pasta. Rellena la masa y dobla los bordes. Espolvorea con semillas y queso rallado y hornea por 20 min. ⚠TIP: con la receta de la masa podes hacer galletitas o grisines! 👌

Perche fabio è un nome italiano" "si mia madre è italiana mentre mio padre è di qui, dove abitavi in italia?" "A milano te?" "Mia madre è di pinerolo in piemonte" ah bello un italiano potrei trovarmi bene con lui inoltre è abbastanza bello: è alto capelli lunghetti marroni, occhi marroni e ha un bellissimo fisico, deve fare atletica mi ricorda matteo il mio ex ragazzo... mi manca moltissimo stavamo molto bene insieme ma ci siamo dovuti lasciare dopo che mi sono trasferita per la distanza... " "ciao io invece sono Gregory" si presenta un altro ragazzo tendendomi la mano, lui dev'essere cubano o brasiliano o cose del genere perchè è scuro di pelle ma.ha i tratti brasiliani sembra "piacere" rispondo strigendogli la mano non mi va di ripetere ancora una volta che il mio nome è luna ormai l'avranno capito.
"Io mi chiamo Jennyfer, sono la ragazza di Gregory" mi dice una ragazza moolto bella vestita con dei pantaloni cargo neri e una maglia vans bianca con la scritta nera, mentre parla si avvicina a gregory che la stringe a se e abbassa la mano fino a toccarle il culo... in questo momento mi manca matteo tantissimo...
"Tu come hai detto che ti chiami?" Mi chiede quella ragazza "luna" le rispondo lei ride  e mi dice "ma che razza di nome è?" Continua a ridere e inizia a.fare movimenti strani assieme a Gregory solo ora noto che sta fumando e ha gli occhi rossi... probabilmente sta fumando una canna. No. Me ne voglio andare. Mio fratellino di 14 anni è finito in coma per aver fumato una sola volta una canna, ed è da otto mesi bloccato in quel letto. Cazzo. Sto ripensando a tutto. Matteo. Simone (mio fratello). Elena (la mia migliore amica). Devo star piangendo perche inizio a vedere tutto sfocato e noto che jacob mi ha messo un braccio intorno alle spalle e mi guarda interrogativo.
Ehiii ecco il 5 capitolo😉💗
Come sempre vi chiedo di dirmi che ne pensate😊👇♥️

The best vegan fish and chips you will ever find. No contest! This is the battered tofu and chips with pea purée and lemon curd from @by1847 in Bristol. The tofu is fried in a light batter with seaweed to give it the slightly salty fishy edge and it works perfectly with the sauces. As you can see @rosietod in the background couldn't wait for me to take a pic to dig in! 😂 I would honestly eat this meal everyday if I could but it is a tad on the pricey side and we paid about £11.50. The portions are small but they do fill you up even though someone with greedy eyes like me never thinks a portion this size is enough! Im currently uploading this while procrastinating from packing as I'm moving house tomorrow to near Bath! 🏡 I'm almost packed but I still have a few bits to sort through and wet clothes to sort out in the morning and I'm also hoping I can fit it all in my little car 🚙 (that actually looks like my car 😆). Hopefully after moving I will head to my fajita dinner party to celebrate if all goes well :D wish me luck! 💫

location: {u'slug': u'breaking-bread-bakery', u'id': u'245434648', u'name': u'Breaking Bread Bakery', u'has_public_page': True}
caption:
For the past half-decade, Breaking Bread has been concocting homemade loaves of bread, fresh pastries, croissants, and baked goods, in their spacious bakery overlooking Higuera Street in Downtown SLO!  There are 4-5 artisan breads baked daily, according their weekly Monday through Friday schedule. Today being Thursday, I walked into the aroma of freshly-baked Bordeaux Sourdough, French Baguettes, Honey, and (Baker's Choice) Fig Pecan loaves. 
Turning my attention to their lunch options, I found that they offer Mediterranean, Greek, Power, Cobb, and Chef's salads, in their cold case, made daily with varied greens, vegetables, protein, and toppings, every morning.  What caught my eye was their sandwiches, served on your choice of bread, and also their daily soup offerings.  I opted for a half of the classic BLT, on their Bordeaux Sourdough, and a cup of their Hungarian Cauliflower soup, served with a slice of bread.  Their Honey bread was highly recommended, having just come out of the oven.  I was thoroughly delighted to find it not only still warm, but so flavorful, with just a hint of sweetness from the honey.  The spongy center, combined with crunch of the crust, transported my taste buds back to the Village bakeries I visited in provincial France several years ago.  The soup was seasoned with paprika, and included carrots and a few other vegetables in the broth, along with the cauliflower. 
The 1/2 sandwich is just about $2 less than the whole, which normally goes for $6.91.  The cup of soup, with a slice of bread is $3.94, so my total spend was $9.60.
I couldn't resist and also purchased two of their homemade cookies - a decadent Brown Butter Chocolate Chip and a Ginger Sparkles, with sprinkles of crystallized sugar atop, for $1.25 each.

location: {u'slug': u'loja-ecuador', u'id': u'236041898', u'name': u'Loja, Ecuador', u'has_public_page': True}
caption:
Los mugcakes son tortitas hechas en una taza y en el microondas. Son perfectos para ese antojo dulce de media tarde o para esas mañanas en las que no hay tiempo 🏃 porque hacerlos toma menos de 5 minutos, en serio!! 💁 .
.
🍮 MUGCAKE de ZANAHORIA 🍮
.
.
Batir en un taza honda durante 1 minuto:
- 1 huevo
- endulzante al gusto @stevialifeec
Luego agregar:
- 1/2 ctda. de vainilla en polvo (o líquida)
- 1 ctda. de aceite de coco @lifechoice_
- 2 cdas. de leche de almendras sin azúcar @naturesheart_ec (o la que tengas a mano)
- 1/4 tz. de zanahoria rallada
Mezcla bien y agregar:
- 3 cdas. de harina de avena @quaker (harina integral de trigo, de coco o de almendra también funcionan)
- 1/4 ctda. de polvo de hornear
- 1/2 ctda. de canela en polvo
- 2 nueces troceadas
Revolver hasta que se integre todo y llevar al microondas por 1:45 minutos.
*Puedes ir probando cada 30 segundos hasta conseguir la consistencia deseada (es mejor que quede suavito a que se cocine mucho).
Dejar enfriar unos minutos antes de servir o puedes comer directo de la taza 😉
.
.
Topping: yogurt vegano de almendras @dhoyogurtvegano (reemplazable por yogurt natural o griego), canela en polvo, pasas picadas finito y nuez 😋

Always amazes me how restaurants just do what the frig they like with your food 😤 asked for the fish with nothing except veg, no butter and got a heap of pink shite on top - I didn’t eat it but I’m guessing it was carrying a few syns. All in all a successful day of not being in control of my meals as much as I would have liked; made sensible choices where I could (apart from the biscuits 😂) but really glad that I didn’t blow it and give in to snacks on the train, cake and late in the cafe, pork belly on tonight’s menu, the second packet of biscuits in the hotel room! I’ve been on the road since 7am so I’m well and truly ready for my beauty sleep!! Night slimming worldies 😴

Receta del budin! Ideal para desayunos y meriendas. Para los amigos veganos y vegetarianos!!
👉Mezcla en un bowl una taza de harina integral tamizada, una taza de harina de avena (procesa la avena común, pizca de sal, una cucharada sopera de polvo para hornear.
👉En otro bowl pisa tres bananas grandes maduras, una cucharada de canela en polvo y chia activada (una cucharada sopera de semillas y 5 de agua, mezcla y deja reposar unos minutos)
👉Por otro lado, mezcla media taza de aceite con un cuarto de taza de azúcar mascabo, podes agregar ralladura de cítricos y/o esencia de vainilla a gusto.
👉Incorporar las bananas pisadas a la preparacion de aceite y azúcar y esta última a la de los secos.
👉Cocinar en horno pre calentado a 180 por 45 50 minutos o hasta que introduciendo un palito este salga seco. Dejar entibiar antes de comer.

location: {u'slug': u'bonn-germany', u'id': u'107481562', u'name': u'Bonn, Germany', u'has_public_page': True}
caption:
My newest creation. Sauteed salmon, spelt penne with a creamy sauce and cavolo nero (black cabbage, an italian speciality) with tomato and dry fried peanuts.
I bought the cabbage at the farmer's market today and wanted to use it right away. The cabbage tastes fantastic. Not bitter or too strong. More like a mix of cabbage, turnip greens and spinach. And it stayed crunchy even after blanching. A great meal! And for all of you, who don't like fish: the dish will work with chicken, or without meat at all! 😉
I blanched the cabbage first, took it out of the water and aside and then cooked the pasta in the same water. That saves space and energy and gives a great taste to the pasta. When the pasta was ready, I poured out the water, readded the cabbage. Then I added the sliced tomato and the peanuts. The sauce was prepared in a different pot and I poured it over the pasta/cabbage, reheated everything and then served it woth the salmon.

@Regranned from @petit_fit - ¡EY CHIPIRÓN, TODOS LOS DÍAS SALE EL SOL CHIPIRÓN! 🦑☀️¿Cómo ha ido vuestro día? El mío un no parar, pero ahora es momento de relajarse 😌 Hoy os dejo una cena súper sencillita y que se me llevaba antojando desde hace unos días, la receta es de mi petitmamá con algunas modificaciones 😋 ¿Queréis ver el relleno? Deslizad el dedo 😏👉🏼
.
CHIPIRONES RELLENOS DE VERDURAS EN SALSA DE TOMATE CASERA 🦑🍅
.
INGREDIENTES PARA DOS PERSONAS:
🔸12 chipirones frescos.
🔸1/2 pimiento rojo.
🔸1/2 pimiento verde.
🔸1/2 cebolla dulce.
🔸1/2 calabacín.
🔸1 puñado de champiñones.
🔸250 gr de tomate natural triturado.
🔸1 cda de semillas de sésamo ecológicas caramelizadas con tomate, kale y cebolla.
🔸1 cdita de AOVE.
🔸Pimienta negra.
🔸Sal rosa del Himalaya.
.
PROCESO:
🔸Lavamos y cortamos las verduras en trozos pequeños.
🔸Rehogamos las verduras en una cazuela con un poquito de AOVE y añadimos las patas de los chipirones.
🔸Cuando las verduras y las patas estén doraditas los incorporamos dentro de los chipirones y lo cerramos con un palillo.
🔸Rehogamos los chipirones con un poquito de AOVE en una cazuela, tapamos y dejamos reducir hasta que se consuma el agua que sueltan.
🔸Incorporamos el tomate natural triturado, salpimentamos y dejamos cocinar durante 5-10 minutos más a fuego medio y removiendo de vez en cuando.
🔸Los retiramos del fuego, les quitamos los palillos y añadimos el sesamo caramelizado.
.
Una que se va a ir prontio a la cama ¡Buenas noches chipirones! 🦑😘
.

caption:
Локация №4, FARШ на Лубянке.
Признаться, очень трудно написать что-то осмысленное после того, как в течение получаса тобой владели первобытные инстинкты хищника. Настолько вкусный ужин у меня был, пожалуй, много миллионов лет назад, когда упавший метеорит довел слишком медленного мамонта до состояния medium-прожарки. 
Но хватит воспоминаний, оцениваем! Изумительная булочка, потрясающая котлетка, бодрая музыка - практически одни плюсы; разве что хотелось бы чуть большего простора, потому что рассесться там компанией будет уже проблематично. 9 динозавровых когтей из 10, и то потому, что десятый коготь я сейчас облизываю. Пока это лучшая локация из тех, что я посетил в Москве.

LIVE IN BERLIN - DAY 11 PART 3
In un soffio di metro eravamo in Friedrichstraße al #checkpointcarlie . #berlino riusciva a modificare la percezione del tempo e dello spazio. Le distanze sembravano infinite guardandole sulla mappa, mentre invece tutto era raggiungibile in un lampo e il continuo cambio di metro non faceva soffrire nemmeno tanto il freddo. Ne sapeva qualcosa il soldato che stava impalato a presidio del famoso posto di blocco: tra una foto e l'altra con i turisti, si soffiava di continuo il naso che era diventato rosso, gli occhi erano nascosti da Ray Ban da aviatore, camuffando così il suo stato di salute. A parte l'armadio a muro conciato male in mezzo alla strada, quel posto non era nulla di che e mi venne la curiosità di vedere gli altri Checkpoint, ma si trovavano molto fuori città.
LIVE IN BERLIN - DAY 11 PART 4
Salivamo di nuovo sul tappeto volante giallo della bvg: i miei amici romani andavano verso casa, io verso #grosserstern, da me ribattezzata “la rotonda della morte”. Ai piedi della #colonnadellavittoria facevo amicizia con due ragazze romane, due sorelle in vacanza. Si pagava tre euro per salire in cima, con tante scale e ripide; ma la vista dall'alto era uno spettacolo, nonostante il brutto tempo sbiadisse i contorni. Sarei dovuta andare in un giorno sereno, senza né pioggia né troppo sole, e aggiungevo alla lista un'altra scusa per tornare a #berlino. Con le ragazze ci saremmo riviste su Kottbusser Tor al #monarchpub , uno dei loali frequentati da #davidbowie e #iggypop nel loro periodo berlinese. Lo avevo trovato sotto la voce “dove andare la sera”.

My friend, Sithuthukile Mkhwanazi requested that I come and lend her support with something something. Venue #Protea Balalaika #Hotel. Have not been there in over a decade. When the Village Walk was still a place to occasionally check out. Then my buddy Mpho Kgosietsile from Bots happened to be in the same neighbourhood. A little break from work over #dinner was just what the doctor ordered for both of us. Our coy waiter Arnold failed hopelessly at being the #photographer. He tried. So we took over. Catching up. Dinner great. Had a little fun #photoshoot to the amusement of the staff dotted around the #reception area watching us. What to whilst we are waiting for Sthu. 
Then my system turned. Damn. Something that I am #allergic to was in the dinner. The hue of the evening changed. This is why I end up going to the same restaurants where "Everybody knows my name' (Cheers theme song). And most importantly know my dietary requirements. And never cheat by sneaking things in because they think you are just being fussy or forget #food groups! My tolerance levels have plummeted. No wiggle room. Am in agony and discomfort. My poor system has much work to do. Tara, I miss your vigilance about every ingredient that goes into my meal preparations. Needless to say, a real downer ending to a fantastic catch up session with my buddy Mpho. Looking forward to seeing you sooner than later with my two other favourite people. They know who they are. Hugs

🥒 THANK YOU SHERWOOD FOR HAVING US! 🍇

The food market on Woodthorpe park has been running for 3 months now! We have all had great fun selling to you and making food for you. On behalf of the stall holders and myself obviously thanks for making it possible. Pretty much all the traders are local to the area. Mapperley, Sherwood, Arnold and Woodthorpe residents. So we have achieved something very unique. A local market with local sellers. We’d love it if you all attended on Saturday to celebrate our 3 month celebration 🍾 bring your kids, dogs, and join us for coffee and cake on the park to chat about where we go from here and what to expect at Christmas!! Ceviz büyüklüğünde köfteler yapıp, hafif yağladığınız fırın tepsisinde 200 derecede pişirin. ⭐Patlıcanların kabuklarını geniş aralıklı olarak alacalı soyun ve uzunlamasına ince dilimlere ayırın. Hafif yağda pembeleşene kadar kızartın ve fazla yağını kağıt havlu ile alın. Derin bir kaseye kızaran patlıcan dilimlerinden çaprazlamasına koyun ve ortasına bir adet köfte koyup dilimleri üzerine kapatın. Yani köfteyi patlıcanla bohçalar gibi saracaksınız. Ardından fırın tepsisine kaseyi ters çevirerek kapatın ve üzerine bir dilim domates, bir dilim yeşil biber koyup bir kürdan geçirerek sabitleyin. ⭐Bütün patlıcan ve köfteleri bu şekilde hazırlayın. Salçayı sulandırıp tuz, baharat ve yağ ekleyip karıştırdıktan sonra hazırladığınız kebapların üzerinden gezdirerek dökün ve 180 derecede 10 -15 dakika kadar pişirin.

RECEITA DE CANJICA VEGAN:

Ingredientes.

500g de milho para canjica
2 litros de água
1 lata de leite condensado de soja
400 ml de leite de coco
500ml  de bebida de Arroz e Coco
Paus de canela
Canela em pó
Cravos-da-índia
Açúcar de Coco 
Modo de preparar:

Deixar a canjica de molho na água durante a noite.
Cozinhe a #canjica na água do molho em uma panela de pressão por cerca de 1 hora. Quando estiver macia, junte o leite condensado de soja, o leite de coco, a bebida de arroz, a canela em pau e o cravo. Cozinhe em fogo baixo por mais uns 15 minutos. Coloque mais açúcar se quiser. Está pronto a servir. Bom apetite!
Poderá comprar os ingredientes em : www.lojanatural.com.pt

Chia seeds are loaded with nutrients, benefiting your brain and entire body. A single Tbsp. of Chia seeds provides 3g of protein, 3g of healthy fat, and 5g of carbohydrates (all of which comes from fiber). Chia seeds contain calcium, manganese, magnesium, phosphorus, Zinc, potassium, and Vitamins B1, B2, and B3. Chia seeds support healthy bones and may lower the risk of heart disease and type 2 diabetes. The Aztecs and Myans even used chia seeds to fuel performance! (Much better than that sugary sports drink). In addition, chia seeds are high in Omega 3's. However, most of the Omega 3's are in the form of ALA, rather than EPA and DHA
.
Incorporate chia seeds into your diet by mixing them in oats, smoothies, and yogurt. Does anyone else have creative ways they like to eat chia seeds? I'd love to hear. Comment below!

Je partage une autre photo de mon plat préféré cheveux d'ange à la vapeur. Ce plat est un classique de la gastronomie tunisien
دويدة مفورة بالعلوش محرحرة
_____________________________________________

ingrédients :
-500 gr cheveux d'anges
-viande
-4 tomate
-1 petit oignon
-pois chiches
-1 poivron
-2 pommes de terre
-tête d'ail
-huile
-250g de concentré de tomates
-1c harissa arbi 
Préparation
1)assaisonner la viande 30 mn à  l'avance (Sel.Poivre noire.curcuma.poivre rouge)
2)remplir le bas de couscoussier avec de l'eau et mettre au feu 
3)dans un bol, bien mélanger avec les mains, les cheveux d'ange avec 3c d'huile
4)Mettre les pâtes dans le haut du couscoussier 
5)Dans une marmite, Faire revenir l’oignon, l’ail, le poichiche et la viande dans l'huile  jusqu’à ce que l'oigon devient translucide
6)sortir la viande et réserver
7)éplucher et broyer les tomates (ou couper en petit dés) et ajouter à la marmite
8)mélanger le concentré de tomate  et la harissa avec un verre d'eau bien chaud et ajouter à la marmite
8)laisser cuire à feu doux pendant 20 à 30 toujours en remuant. (moi je goûte un peu sur le bout de la langue  pour voir s'il y a encore ou non l'acidité de la tomate)
9)assaisonner la sauce (piment rouge, 1/2 curcuma, sel et poivre)
10)ajouter la viande et 3 verres d'eau bien chaud à la sauce et laisser cuire
11)ajouter de temps en temps une louche de sauce aux cheveux d'ange et mélanger 
12)La sauce doit cuire entre 30 et 40 minutes, si vous trouvez qu’au cours de ce temps, elle devient trop concentrée ou qu’elle va bruler, ajouter de l’eau et laisser mijoter (vous pouvez ajouter maintenant les pomme de terre si non vous pouvez les frire)
14)décorer avec des oeufs et les piments  vert

I have changed the recipe, so quick and easy. These are to die for! Orange, Walnut and choc granola bars! Totally healthy and amazing taste! #lowcarb #lowgidiet #unrefinedsugar #healthyfood #cleaneating  #recipe #food #foodie #snacks #granola #oats 
100g butter
3 tbsp golden syrup
85g demerara sugar
140g porridge oat
½ tsp ground cinnamon
50g desiccated coconut
2 tbsp linseeds, slightly crushed 
1 tbsp sesame seeds
2 grated rind of satsuma or tangerine
100g dark choc
100g lightly crushed walnut halves

Heat oven to 160C/fan 140C/gas 3. Butter a 22cm square baking tin, a false bottom works best. Melt the butter, syrup and sugar in a pan. Pour in the oats, cinnamon, coconut, seeds and nuts, orange rind and chocolate , mix and pour into tin. Bake for 30-35 mins. Leave to cool for 10 mins, then cut into squares, I then put in fridge to firm up more for 1 hr. remove from fridge and they should come away and place in airtight container, Will keep for 1 week.

CARNS⚜️Kulfi At Chattorey Restaurant.

CARN'S is a family run business with 15 years of specialised experience.
Our artisan Malai (Cream) Kulfi is suited to the modern palate in 5 exquisite offerings. 
In 1870 my great grandfather used to make kulfi as a treat for my grandfather and in turn my grandfather made Kulfi as a treat for my father.
I remember the first day that I tasted the Kulfi it was 23 years ago. When I told my dad how great I thought they were he said to me "son you know these would sell like hot cakes" and that's all I needed to hear.
_______________________________
Carn's Kulfi's are artisan.
The unmistakable creamy taste of Carn's originates from a unique composition which is a closely guarded family secret and combined with a choice of high grade ingredients.
Carn's Kulfi's represents substance and no gimmicks. Our quality Kulfi is displayed in transparent wrapping, you can visualise the taste sensation you're about to experience. 
Perfecting the Carn’s Kulfi has always been my mission. This is truly for the Kulfi connoisseurs that is why I make Kulfi's especially for you guys. 
Ask for them by name Carn's Kulfi.  #icecream #carnskulfi #vegetarian #halal

CHOCO BANANA STRUDEL

Bahan:
1 lbr puff pastry instan 
Secukupnya pisang matang,potong bulat
Secukupnya keju
Secukupnya meises
1 sdm skm
1 butir kutel,utk olesan

Cara:
Panaskan oven hingga 200 dercel
Di meja kerja tabur tepung terigu,bentangkan puff pastry,tabur terigu lagi,gilas ringan
Oles skm di tengah sampai rata,tabur meises,tata potongan pisang,tabur meises dan keju
Sayat2 puff pastry di kiri dan kanan,kepang satu persatu hingga menutupi isian, oles dengan kutel
Panggang dlm oven hingga matang keemasan

caption:
Итак, как и обещал пост про плохие шаурмечные в Праге. Надо отметить, хороших мне тут попадалось больше, чем плохих, так что выбор был не прост. Но сугубо по-моему мнению самые плохие это: 1) KPC на народни триде. Место новое и поначалу внушало оптимизм, однако очень быстро скатилось в моих глазах, из-за того что там постоянно не наливают соус, даже если специально за этим следишь. Мясо нормальное, но без соуса это невозможно воспринимать, как шаурму. К тому же в мое последнее посещение там сменился персонал и изменился размер в худшую сторону. 
2) Royal kebab рядом с Лазарской. Место просто отдаёт жуткой антисанитарией и жутко острыми соусами, даже если просишь сделать не острую. Когда там был первый раз - мясо вообще отдавало какой-то собачатиной. 
3) Istanbul kebab на Липанской. Тут пункт очень спорный, ибо шавуха то неплохая. Но структура просто ужасна, разваливается сразу же, и это действительно мешает её есть. А у вас есть тут шаурмечные, в которые не хотелось бы возвращаться?

What I cooked for the week. 
4 hour hard steak re purposed with sherry for 3-6 days hours then slow cooked into sandwiches:
Day1: Turmeric + saffron + caramelized onions with a touch of tagine spice. Slow cooked with binyamina olive oil + a sliver of butter. 
Steak simmered @17500 but for sear then dropped to 5,000 btu in sherry, ginger garlic homemade sauce then a sunny side egg on top when fat has reached proper caramelization. 
Topped with Madison Kaiser sliced bread crunchy side out. 
Side dish: Carrot medly mixed with orange blossom Catskill honey with Lavender, crushed coriander then topped with thyme for the last 3 minutes. 
Day 2+3: Carmelized onions and pepper cooked for max caramelization &  Asian szcechuan spice. Recipe: cook red and green bell with turmeric first + garlic and then add a touch of fish sauce ginger siracha soy, 🍋 szcechuan salt, honey 🍯 + hand crushed  rosemary. Simmer until sauce thickens. Put to the side

Add steak in sherry and simmer down then add onions and peppers on max heat to carm and then simmer while it thickens together tasting to your taste with slight adjustments.

💥CARDIO OR WEIGHTS?💥 post by@syattfitness
.
#Repost @syattfitness (@get_repost)
・・・
🐙The fitness industry runs on a pendulum of extremes. Everything is either good or bad. Right or wrong. Healthy or unhealthy. Fattening or fat burning. Issue is, things aren't that black and white. And creating these false dichotomies is what digs us further into fitness "ruts" that are harder and harder to climb out of.
-
🍕Cardio is the prime example. For a long time, cardio was *it.* THE thing. Everyone ran or biked or swam or roller skated (lol those were the days) or whatever. Weight lifting was "dangerous," not "functional," and only for "meat heads."
-
🍗Recently, though, this all changed. Nowadays weight lifting is the end-all-be-all of fitness, whereas cardio is hated on and made fun of. Hell, I see coaches every day bragging about how they don't do any cardio whatsoever - only heavy lifting - and stay shredded year round.
-
✈️And that's great. It really is. But there's more to fitness than staying shredded. And just because you don't need to do something to get shredded, doesn't mean it won't help. Nor does it mean there aren't a fistful of other benefits. Truth is, both cardio and weights have a ton of benefits, each of which complement the other.
-
🏓Between you and me, I don't want to be a one trick pony. Sure, deadlifting 4x my body weight is great. But I also like running a 6min mile. And not getting winded every time I go up a flight of stairs. And, as weird as it sounds, I like finishing a workout out of breath and sweaty and feeling like I just got worked.
-
🦄For me, strategically doing both weights and cardio is the best way to get the best of both worlds. So you can be strong as all hell, and the fittest one in the room. You don't have to choose - you can do both.
-

caption: TAKING OFF tomorrow! Beyond excited. London, here I come! 🇬🇧

Thursday's 🔥Fat loss🔥 tip! 
What time of day are you most likely to "give in" or go "off track" with your healthy eating plan?

Is it between lunch and dinner?
Is it when you get home from work?
Is it after dinner when cravings strike?

Recognize your "trouble time" causing you to go off track. 
WHY is this time hard for you? 
Are you not prepared?
Is it true hunger or a craving?
Are you keeping foods in the house that aren't supporting your goals?

MAKE YOUR DIET WORK FOR YOU, not the other way around.

Try this --> *CALORIE PARTITIONING*

Partition your calories to the times of the day when you seem to have increased hunger or desire to eat.

My "trouble time" was in the evenings, which is pretty popular for most. So I make my diet work for me by budgeting and "saving" the load of my daily calorie intake for later in the day when I feel like I need them the most to stay in track with my goals. *Again, this is why it's so IMPORTANT to know, understand, and track your daily calorie intake so you can partition your calories accordingly. 
If you're not assessing, you're guessing.

For me, the most important thing is to go to bed on a full stomach. I sleep better and my compliance to my diet is much greater this way. 
I am fine with feeling a little hunger at times throughout the day, knowing that I can fill that hunger later in the day, look forward to a big meal, and go to bed feeling full and satisfied. This keeps me on track and consistent which leads to the results I'm after.

How do I execute this?

I skip breakfast.
Have my first (smaller) meal around 2pm.
Have a LARGE meal around 7pm.
Have another decent size meal at 10pm.
Go to bed. 
That's my "diet" strategy.

It works for ME, and most importantly... I ENJOY IT. 
And dietary adherence + consistency = results. 
So let's say you're like me, and you also struggle with the evenings. For an example, I have 2,000 calories to work with for my total daily intake if I want to lose fat.

An example of "BAD" calorie partitioning:
*Breakfast: 500 calories
*Snack: 300 calories *Lunch: 600 calories
*Snack: 300 calories *Dinner: .... 300 calories?.... yeah right. *This leaves me with ONLY 300..👇🏻👇🏻👇

Привет, ❤ и вперёд.

Думала, думала и надумала.Хочу поделится своей  тренировкой в ДОМАШНИХ УСЛОВИЯХ! Худеть можно везде и всегда. Как я уже говорила.

Количество подходов и раз, подбираете под себя. Все зависит от ваших возможностей. Такую тренировку можно делать с утяжелителями.

Вы видели погоду? К сожалению, не побегаешь, а дорожку купить не каждый сможет. Не так ли?! Вам в помощь придет тренировка ⬇

На раз-два. Поехали ➡. .

Кардио упражнения. 4 сета, в каждом сете разное кол-во упражнений с разным количеством повторений. Перерыв после 4 сетов 1 мин, далее еще сет...и еще. 
Сет #1. ➡ берпи 15 раз + скалолаз 50 раз. 
Сет #2.➡приседания (интенсивные) 15 раз, плие приседы 20 раз + статика 20 сек. 
Сет #3.➡ отжимания 10раз, джампинг джеки 50 раз. 
Сет #4. ➡ прыжки с приседом 20 раз, скручивания по 30 раз. 
Таких 5 кругов, можно меньше.

Повторюсь, тренировки могут быть везде и всегда, главное желание, как бы вы не были заняты, можно найти 30 ➕ минут. Конечно, если у вас проблемы, то посоветуйтесь с врачом. И следите за своим состоянием 😉

Всем продуктивного и хорошего дня несмотря на погоду.

caption: THE best barbecued meats at MAM in Notting Hill, the latest venture from Colin Yu of @salvationinnoodles. Focusing on food and techniques from around Hanoi, the star of the show is the barbecued skewers - think smoky, melty pork belly, tender beef wrapped in betel leaf, fresh, juicy king prawns, and lean, tender chicken. They come on a bed of lettuce leaves, shredded carrot, cucumber and pickled red onion, with a zingy, spicy dip and a set of spongy, woven vermicelli wraps to pile it all up in. Gloriously messy to eat and utterly delicious. Don't miss the fish sauce and garlic chicken wings, coated in a crisp outer shell, or the subtle flavour of their in-house pho. caption:
TEQUILA LIME SALMON SALAD
By @thecookierookie 😋👌
Ingredients
For the Tequila Lime Salmon:
2 salmon filets with skin-on
2 tablespoons olive oil
2 limes, juice and zest
¼ cup tequila
1 (1 oz.) package Old El Paso Taco Seasoning Mix
3 tbsps dark brown sugar
For the Tequila Lime Vinaigrette:
2 tbsps freshly squeezed lime juice
2 tbsps tequila
2 tbsps freshly squeezed orange juice
4 tbsps honey
1 tsp chili powder
¼ cup fresh cilantro, chopped
¼ cup canola oil
For the Salad and Toppings:
¼ head Iceberg lettuce, cleaned and chopped
½ bunch green or red leaf lettuce; cleaned, trimmed & chopped
½ cup chopped fresh tomatoes
½ cup Mexican Blend shredded cheese
1 can black beans, rinsed & drained
1 can sweet corn, rinsed & drained
1 avocado, peeled & sliced or chopped – drizzle with lime juice to keep from browning.
¼ cup fresh cilantro, chopped
Tortilla Strips
Instructions
For the Salmon:
(Salmon can be marinated and kept in fridge up to 24 hours prior to cooking.)
Place olive oil, lime juice, lime zest, tequila, Old El Paso Taco Seasoning Mix and brown sugar in a gallon size Ziploc bag and mix until well incorporated. Add the salmon filets and gently rub the marinade over the salmon. Close the bag and marinate it in the fridge 2-24 hours.
When ready to serve, preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Cover a baking sheet with foil and spray it lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Remove the salmon from the marinade & place it, skin-side down, on the baking sheet.
Place the baking sheet on the middle rack of the oven & roast it for 4-6 mins per half-inch thickness of salmon. Measure the salmon at the thickest part. 4 mins will give you salmon with a pink center (medium-rare) & 6 mins will be thoroughly cooked through.
The salmon is done when it easily flakes apart with a fork. If desired, test the doneness with an instant read thermometer – salmon is considered done at a minimum 145 degrees F at the thickest part of the salmon.
Remove the cooked salmon from the oven & transfer to plate. Remove the skin before placing the salmon on the mixed salad.
For the Salad:
In a large salad bowl, combine the chopped lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, beans & corn. Mix gently.#food #foodie

There is no such thing as a universally standard healthy "look." You may be strong, healthy, and of a sound mental state and not look like a fitness model and that's OKAY. Anytime I've ever personally shredded down to the point where I could see a full 6-8 pack I was doing so like it was a full time job. That amount of time and energy and discipline is certainly commendable but just because you aren't applying the maximum human effort possible does not mean you are unhealthy in any way. I say this all the time, but remember this is your life and you get to choose your experiences. People not never understand your personal battles, your injuries, your allergies, your health conditions, or your circumstances that got you to where you are at this current moment. Be kind to yourself, be patient with yourself, and don't get caught up in comparing yourself. Keep on keeping on 🙌🙌🙌

🎯 DAY SEVEN - BREAKFAST - Quick Banana Pancakes 🍌
Week One done! While physical changes are yet to be revealed, I'm definitely feeling lighter, healthier and happier - I'm in control of my body and what I'm putting into it. This morning it was these easy banana pancakes - 5 ingredients; 5 minutes to prep and 5 minutes to cook.
Recipe:
Blend 1 mashed banana, a pinch of baking powder, a pinch or two of aromatic spice (I used clove but you can use cinnamon, star anise, nutmeg, etc), a pinch of salt and one egg. Blend for about 3-5 seconds (you want it smooth, but not thinned out). Pour into an oiled pan and flip when bubbles appear. I was in a rush this morning but it would have been deeeelish with raspberries and peanut butter!

ビジュアルの良い透き通ったラーメンは鯛の旨味が良く出ている。

紫玉葱はマリネなのか程良い酸味が付いて良いアクセント。
2種類のレアチャーシューはスープを損ねず肉の味だけで充分に楽しめる。
三つ葉の風味も良い！٩( 'ω' )و

I ordered Iced Americano with Heavy Cream. I got whipped cream instead. The barista told me that it's the same thing and I can just mix it myself.

From what I read online, it's not the same. "It’s all about the fat. Heavy cream has a higher fat content than whipping cream, coming in at 36 percent, while whipping cream only requires 30 percent fat. When it comes to fat, six percent makes a difference." .
.
What do you guys do when you order coffee outside? Personally, I'm fine with either but I like Heavy Cream more.

The truth is you can eat whatever you want as long as the quantity of those foods are within your personal allowance of protein, carbs and fats (macronutrients) and in accordance with your fitness goals you are looking to achieve.

The way you go about moderating these foods is to track them throughout the day using a calorie counting app such as myfitnesspal that way you can allow for the foods you personally want to eat whilst staying on track with your fitness goals.

Today's nutrition lecture was on the ketogenic diet in treating epilepsy, and it also addressed other complementary therapies. I am so thankful we had the opportunity to learn from a pediatric neurologist who specializes in drug-resistant epilepsy, as food really can be our medicine. Studies show that ⅔ of patients who failed at least 2 epilepsy drugs have at least a 50% reduction in seizures on a strict ketogenic diet. ⅓ of these patients on keto experience a 90% or greater reduction in seizures. So cool!! Do any of you follow a ketogenic diet? .

Camarones a la parrilla con quinoa tabouli (2 a 4 porciones)
INGRESIENTES
- Tabouli
- ½ Tazas de quínoa
- 1 ½ Tazas de perejil cortado
- ½ Tazas de menta cortada
- ½ Tazas de cebolletas cortadas
- 1 Tomate cortado en cubos
- 1 Pepino inglés pelado y cortado en cubos
- 2 Cucharadas de aceite de oliva extra virgen
- 1 Limón
- ½ Cucharadita de sal
- Camarones
- 1 Libra de camarones crudos , pelados , sin venas
- 2 Cucharadas de cebolla rebanada
- 1 Cucharada de ajo rebanado
- 1 Cucharada de jalapeño rebanado
- 1 Naranja

PREPARACION
1. Cocina la quínoa como dice el paquete. Esparce sobre una charola y deja enfriar en el refrigerador.

2. Combina la quínoa con los ingredientes del tabouli en un bowl y refrigera.

3. Calienta el asados a fuego medio y alto.

4. Mezcla los camarones con los demás ingredientes y deja marinar por 30 minutos.

5. Cocina los camarones por 2 minutos de un lado y 1 minuto del otro lado.

6. Acomoda los camarones sobre la quinoa.

Saltado de quinua con verduras🍃

INGREDIENTES:
- 1/2 cebolla picada
- 1 cdta de ajo picado
- aceite de oliva
- 1 tomate picado
- 1/4 pimiento picado
- 1/2 brocoli picado
- 1/2 tz de zanahoria rallada
- 1/2 docena de huevos de codorniz
- 1/2 tz de choclo - 1 tz de quinua
- sillao
- aceite de ajonjolí o sésamo - sal y pimienta
- 2 cdrs de azúcar 
PREPARACIÓN:
1. Poner a sancochar la quinua, yo lo hago en la olla arrocera y queda perfecto, 1tz de quinua por 1 tz de agua, sal, ajo y aceite.
2. Poner a sancochar los huevos de codorniz en agua hirviendo x 4min, sacar del agua caliente y dejarlos reposar 1min en agua fría para que la cáscara salga rápido.
3. En un wok ponemos un poco de aceite de oliva y freímos el ajo y la cebolla primero, luego agregamos el brocoli, pimientos, zanahorias y lo removemos por unos 5min para que se cocinen todas las verduras, por último le agregamos el tomate y el choclo ya sancochado y Sal pimentamos. 
4. En nuestro saltado de verduras agregamos la quinua ya cocida mezclamos de manera homogénea y agregamos un poco de aceite de ajonjolí y sillao al gusto.
5. Una vez mezclado todo agregamos 2cdras de azúcar volvemos a mezclar y le agregamos los huevos de codorniz.
6. Ya con todos los ingredientes incorporados podemos servir!😋🍴🍃 Nosotros lo hemos acompañado con una ensalada de col y zanahoria, puedes acompañarlo de cualquier ensalada fresca!

El afamado Martín Berasategui Olazábal con 8 estrellas michelin nació el 27 de abril de 1960 en San Sebastián. Estudió en el Colegio de los Padres Capuchinos de Lekaroz, en el Valle de Baztan(Navarra). A los trece años comenzó a trabajar en el restaurante familiar, Bodegón Alejandro.

En 1979, empezó sus estudios de hostelería en la escuela de pastelería moderna de Yssingeaux, donde conoció a diversos chefs internacionales. En 1981, se convirtió en responsable De Bodegón Alejandro, que recibió su primera estrella Michelin en 1986.En 1993 abrió su primer restaurante, llamado "Martín Berasategui", en Lasarte-Oria.

En tres años, el local recibió dos estrellas Michelin.A partir de ahí el cocinero recibió un diversos premios, entre ellos el Premio Euskadi de Gastronomía al Mejor Cocinero de Euskadi en 1998 y el Tambor de Oro de San Sebastián en 2005.En 1996, decidió crear una asociación empresarial, el Grupo Martín Berasategui, para hacerse cargo de restaurantes tales como el Bodegón Alejandro, el restaurante del Guggenheim de Bilbao o el Kursaal Martín Berasategui.

El grupo empresarial se encuentra disuelto, pero sigue asesorando a varios restaurantes[5]​ como Hotel Condes de Barcelona, Loidi y Lasarte; restaurante Fonda España; restaurante Doma de Bilbao; restaurante MB del Hotel Abama de Tenerife o los restaurantes Tempo y Passion by Martín Berasategui en México y en Punta Cana.#michelin#martinberasategui#michelinstar#food#foodporn#garrote#themichelinguide

caption:
Dearest Bay Area Friends,
.
As you know, many folks have lost their homes in the Northern California fires over the last few days. Our Team, has been in touch with the Petaluma Community Center which is a hub for fire victims and they are in immediate need of the following items. (Many of which can be found at the Dollar Store):
.
Blankets
New pillows
New underwear (all ages)
Socks
Baby formula
Bottles
Baby food
Toiletries (toothbrushes, toothpaste, soap, deodorant)
Diapers and wipes
Pet food
Pet bowls 
Brushes and Combs
Coloring books
Crayons
Children's books
Towels
Latex gloves and masks
Reusable bags
Clothes (maybe it’s time for a Fall closet clean out for donation?) .
We realize this is short notice, but if you would like to donate, please drop off your items to the Office at 100 Pasito Terrace, Sunnyvale, CA, 94086 by this Friday morning. .
All donations will transported to the Petaluma Community Center this Friday.
.
Have a great rest of the week and we appreciate your participation in regards to all families effected. .
XO Grant Society Team

Hello tout le monde 🙋🏼aujourd'hui je vous retrouve dans ce post assez particulier. 🍃Constamment à la recherche de moins de sucre , sans sucre même , les marques diététiques savent comment nous attirer l'œil avec leurs gros titres "moins 50 % " -65% de sucre en moins" . Mais par quoi est substitué le sucre? Est ce que nous nous ferions pas berner, manipulé ? Se substituant est il "sain"?
Sain j'entends , quelque chose de naturel comme le sucre roux ou le miel ...
En achetant une tablette d'une certaines marques , celle ci m'a attiré car elle me promettait être à 95% de chocolat . Mais en la  mangeant j'ai une la bonne idée de regarder sa composition . Certes il n y a pas de sucre mais du "polyols" . En effectuant des recherches , le polyols est un substituant du sucre moins calorique que le sucre . Se substituant est synthétisé en laboratoire 🔬. Ce fût le mot qui me retourna l'estomac . Laboratoire . Créer de toute pièce. L'image de souris et de test surgir. Manger sainement devient poison. On cherche à manger moins calorique mais sachez que le produit supprimé est toujours compensé! Et très mal ! On ingère des éléments sans savoir leur composition qui est tellement pas naturel. Manger "sainement" c'est pas supprimer mais manger des aliments naturels et non transformés. Ma tablette que j'achetais en super marché non diététique est plus saine que celle diététique, il n' y a pas photo. Faites et soyez vigilants lorsque vous consommez des produits diététiques , on. Oui fait croire que c'est bon mais au final on ne connaît pas la composition . Nous sommes ignorant et nous laissons manipulé par la société de consommation . 
Je fais ce post à toute ces personnes qui veulent : rééquilibrer leur alimentation , faire un régime ... se sont des éléments à ne pas négliger. #blog #instagram #healthy #food #anarecovery #sain #nourriture #diet #dietetique #recette #motivation

XO Kerilyn Grant

Want to quickly get lean? Ditch the carbs. Check out these Grilled Chicken Caesar Wraps ❤️
.
By @cleanfoodcrush
.
makes about 8-10 wraps/4-5 servings 
Ingredients:
1 Head Romaine Lettuce 
1.2 lbs. Chicken Tenders 
1.5 cups Cherry Tomatoes, sliced
1/4 Cup Parmesan Cheese – grated 
1 Tbs. Garlic Powder 
1 Tbs. Italian Seasoning 
Sea Salt and Pepper to taste 
Avocado Oil, or Olive Oil 
Greek Yogurt Caesar Dressing:
Juice from 1 fresh lemon 
2 Tbsp soy sauce, or coconut aminos 
1 Tbsp raw honey 
1 Tsp dijon mustard 
1/2 cup Greek yogurt 
Instructions:
Whisk all dressing ingredients together until combined and smooth. 
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. 
Sprinkle chicken tenders with garlic powder, Italian seasoning, sea salt and pepper - rub to coat evenly.
Preheat a large grill pan or outdoor grill over medium-high heat. rub grill with 2 Tbsp. oil.
Grill the chicken for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until cooked through. 
Prepare 8-10 large leaves of romaine lettuce. 
Once the chicken has cooked and cooled, add a couple of tenders to each romaine leave. Then top with a few cherry tomatoes, drizzle 
with 2 Tbsp of Caesar dressing and sprinkle with parmesan. 
Serve with lemon wedges.

Beef Yakiniku ala @silvialim18
.
Bumbu untuk marinate:
1 sdm kecap asin
1/2 sdm saus tiram
1/2 sdm kecap manis
Merica bubuk sesuai selera
.
Bahan:
250 gr daging sapi has dalam, iris tipis
3 siung bawang putih, cincang halus
1 bh bawang bombay, iris2
3 bh cabe rawit merah, iris2
1 sdm kecap inggris
1 sdm minyak wijen
1 sdt gula pasir
150 ml air panas
1 sdm tepung sagu/maizena
.
Steps:
1. Marinate irisan daging sapi dgn bumbu marinate. Biarkan kurleb 15 menit, setelah itu berikan 1 sdm tepung sagu/maizena, aduk rata.
2. Panaskan teflon hingga cukup panas, masukkan sdikit minyak lalu tumis bawang putih hingga wangi. Setelah itu masukkan irisan daging sapi, masak dan aduk2 hingga berubah warna. Masukkan minyak wijen+kecap inggris+gula, biarkan mendidih sbntar lalu aduk cepat. 
3. Diamkan dagingnya sbntar sperti saat panggang daging di teflon, lalu tambahkan irisan bwg bombay+rawit merahnya, aduk rata.
4. Terakhir masukkan air panas, masak hingga mendidih, icip dan koreksi rasanya. Masak hingga air sedikit susut. Angkat dan sajikan.
